total_think_aloud_count.name: Think Aloud Events
total_think_aloud_count.description: The quantity of verbal utterances recorded from a session.

total_search_count.name: Search Events
total_search_count.description: The quantity of search events performed in a session.

total_topic_change_count.name: Topic changes
total_topic_change_count.description: The number of detected topics that occur in a session.

total_mouse_hover_count.name: Mouse Hovers
total_mouse_hover_count.description: The quantity of events where a mouse is hovering over a document.

total_draging_count.name: Dragging Events
total_draging_count.description: The quantity of documents being moved on the interface.

total_open-doc_count.name: Document Open Events
total_open-doc_count.description: The number of document open events performed in a session.

total_reading_count.name: Reading Events
total_reading_count.description: The number of events charcterized as reading.

total_highlight_count.name: Highlight events
total_highlight_count.description: The quantity of highlight events performed in a session.

total_connection_count.name: Connection Events
total_connection_count.description: The quantity of documents being connected to eachother in a session.

total_create_note_count.name: Note Creation Events
total_create_note_count.description: The number of notes created in a session.

total_add_note_count.name: Note Modification Events
total_add_note_count.description: The number of edits performed on a note in a session.

think_aloud_ratio.name: Proportion Think Aloud
think_aloud_ratio.description: The Proportional amount of think aloud events occring in a session.

search_ratio.name: Proportion Search Events
search_ratio.description: The Proportional amount of search events occring in a session.

topic_change_ratio.name: Proportion Topic Changes
topic_change_ratio.description: The Proportional amount of topic change events occring in a session.

mouse_hover_ratio.name: Proportion Hover Events
mouse_hover_ratio.description: The Proportional amount of Mouse Hover events over a documnet in a session.

draging_ratio.name: Proportion Drag Events
draging_ratio.description: The Proportional amount of document movement events in a session.

open-doc_ratio.name: Proportion Doc Opens
open-doc_ratio.description: The Proportional amount of document open events in a session.

reading_ratio.name: Proportion Reading Events
reading_ratio.description: The Proportional amount of reading events in a session.

highlight_ratio.name: Proportion Highlight Events
highlight_ratio.description: The Proportional amount of highlight events in a session.

connection_ratio.name: Proportion Connection Events
connection_ratio.description: The Proportional amount of document connection events in a session.

create_note_ratio.name: Proportion Note Creations
create_note_ratio.description: The Proportional amount of Note creation events in a session.

add_note_ratio.name: Proportion Note Edits
add_note_ratio.description: The Proportional amount of Note modification events in a session.

total_interaction_count.name: Interaction Events
total_interaction_count.description: The number of events recorded for a session regardless of type.

total_duration.name: Session Duration (seconds)
total_duration.description: The time of the last recorded interaction in an interaction log in micro seconds

repeat_searches.name: Search Repetitions
repeat_searches.description: Records the number of searches that are exact matches. Not necessarily how many searches return the same results, but how many searches are an exact string match.

prop_repeat_searches.name: Proportion of Repeated Searches
prop_repeat_searches.description: Records the ratio of searches that are exact matches. Out of all the searches run, what proportion is the exact same string of text.

search_term_similarity.name: Term Similarity
search_term_similarity.description: Using SpaCy's Similarity function, this records how similar words are to each other. Averaged over the entire session, to determine a relative amount of similarity between different terms.

search_time_std_dev.name: Search Burstiness
search_time_std_dev.description: The standard deviation in when a search is conducted in an analysis session. When values are high, it means there is lots of variation in when searches are conducted, thus they are likely more clumped together in time.

search_open_overlap.name: Search Rigor
search_open_overlap.description: The ratio of the average number of documents explored between search events. A value of 1, means that, on average, a user opened every document returned from each of their searches before conducting a new search.

search_term_efficiency.name: Search Broadness
search_term_efficiency.description: The average number of documents returned for the searches conducted by the individual. High numbers here mean the user had many documents returned per search.
